---
import '~/styles/global.css';
import Layout from '~/layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '~/layouts/Header.astro';
import Footer from '~/layouts/Footer.astro';
import LinkButton from '~/components/LinkButton.astro';

// images
import kd3Img from '~/assets/KD-3/render v5 alive-min.png';
// import midiConnectImg from '~/assets/midi_connect/screenshot.png';
---

<Layout title="Wavy Industries - KD-3">
	<main>
		<Header />
		<section class="hero">
			<div class="hero-inner">
				<h1>KD-3</h1>
				<p class="tagline">A portable 3-octave Bluetooth MIDI keyboard with <u>months</u> of battery life</p>
			</div>
		</section>

		<div class="hero-image hero-image--full">
			<img id="kd-3-img" src={kd3Img.src} alt="KD-3" />
		</div>

		<section class="intro">
			<div class="container">
				<div class="intro-content">
					<p>KD-3 results from a multi-year development effort towards a MIDI keyboard which finaly makes Bluetooth practical to use in a music making enviroment. KD-3 is deeply techically grounded, resulting in unheard of battery life (>500 hours) while still delivering very low latency. Charge for 15 minutes to get >100 hours of juice.</p>
					<p>The hardware further reflects our passion for long lasting and thoughtful design, heavily inspired by Braun and Dieter Rams design philosophy. KD-3 is simple by design. All of the controls are hands on and direct. No menu diving here. A ultra low powered screen gives you simple information like battery percentage and connection status. It's body is machined from a single piece of aluminium and anodized in natural color, resulting in a pure and matte finish. Get access to all of it's internals only through a handful of standard screws, making it very easy to service.</p>
					<p>
						We are a small team and with limited resources. KD-3 has been used internally since April 2024, but never reached the hands of customers. If you are interested in participating in a limited edittion production run then don't hesitate to contact us.
					</p>
					<p><i>Please reach out if your're interested.</i></p>
					<p class="section-links">
						<LinkButton id="something-special-kd3" type="default" >Contact</LinkButton>
					</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>
	</main>
	<Footer />
</Layout>

<style>

main {
	background-color: #fff;
	min-height: 100vh;
	display: flex;
	flex-direction: column;
}

img {
	width: 100%;
}

.container {
	max-width: 1200px;
	margin: 0 auto;
	padding: 0 24px;
}

.hero {
	width: 100%;
	padding: 40px 24px 32px;
	color: #111;
}

.hero-inner {
	max-width: 1200px;
	margin: 0 auto;
}

h1 {
	margin: 0 0 8px 0;
	font-weight: 300;
	font-size: 64px;
	line-height: 1.1;
}

.tagline {
	font-size: 18px;
	font-weight: 300;
	color: #555;
	margin: 0 0 24px 0;
	line-height: 1.4;
}

.hero-image {
	width: 100%;
	padding: 50px 10%;
}

.hero-image--full {
	padding: 0;
	height: clamp(260px, 40vw, 520px);
	display: flex;
	align-items: center;
	overflow: hidden;
}

.hero-image--full img {
	width: 100%;
	height: 100%;
	object-fit: cover;
	object-position: center;
}

.intro {
	width: 100%;
	padding: 48px 0;
}

.intro-content {
	max-width: 680px;
	margin: 0 auto;
	text-align: center;
	font-weight: 300;
	color: #444;
}

.intro-content p {
	font-size: 17px;
	line-height: 1.6;
	margin: 0 0 20px 0;
	color: #444;
}

.intro-content p:last-child {
	margin-bottom: 0;
}

.section-links {
	margin-top: 12px;
}

@media (max-width: 768px) {
	h1 {
		font-size: 48px;
	}

	.tagline {
		font-size: 16px;
	}

	.container {
		padding: 0 20px;
	}

	.hero {
		padding: 32px 20px 24px;
	}

	.intro {
		padding: 32px 0;
	}
}
</style>

<script>

function doSomethingSpecial() {
	let special = document.getElementById('something-special-kd3') as HTMLAnchorElement;
	let special1 = "hell"
	let special2 = "o"
	special.href = "mai" + "lto:" + special1 + special2 + "@"+ "wavyindustries.com";
}
setTimeout(doSomethingSpecial, 1000);
</script>
